Feeling tired and exhausted?
Try this❗️

Ingredients:-
1cup greek yogurt or curd
5/6 soaked black raisins 
2tsp soaked basil seeds

Greek yogurt/curd:
>If you are looking for an energy boost, yogurt should be your go to food. 
>Rich in vitamins and minerals, curd is an energy booster. 
>It works as an antioxidant and helps faster recovery.

Black raisins:
>Raisins are packed with energy and rich in fiber, vitamins, and minerals.
>Raisins are naturally sweet and high in sugar and calories, but they're beneficial to our health when eaten in moderation.

Basil seeds:
>Minerals are not often spoken about. But they are essential for energy, metabolism, and sleep. 
>Basil seeds are rich in iron, calcium, and magnesium–all of which are very important for your bone health, red blood cell production, and muscle repair.

Gut Reset – Episode 30
Spiced Buttermilk 🌿🍋

A soothing and refreshing drink for your gut, made with probiotic-rich yogurt and the goodness of curry leaves, coriander leaves, and a hint of ginger. Perfect to aid digestion and keep your gut calm and happy!

Recipe:
🥄 1 cup yogurt (curd)
🌿 A handful of fresh curry leaves
🌿 A handful of fresh coriander leaves
🌱 A small piece of ginger
💧 Water as needed
🧂 Salt to taste

Blend curry leaves, coriander, and ginger with water. Mix this with yogurt and salt. Serve chilled for a delicious gut-loving refresher!

Drink daily to support smooth digestion and overall gut health.

Apple Kiwi Gut Cooler 🍏🥝
